The Kwara State government has approved N21 million as refund to pilgrims, who trav­elled with the state Muslim Pil­grims Welfare Board for 2019 pilgrimage to Saudi Arabia. Executive Secretary of the Board, Alhaji Mohammed Tunde-Jimoh, who disclosed this in a statement in llorin on Tuesday, said the money was approved by the state governor, AbdulRahman AbdulRasaq. Tunde-Jimoh explained that the amount approved as refund for the pilgrims was returned by the Saudi author­ities for the services not ren­dered to the pilgrims during their stay in the Holy Land. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network He added that the refund in­cluded the intending pilgrims, who paid part of the Hajj fare, but incapacitated to make the trip due to one reason or the other. He said that the refund would also take care of the de­ceased pilgrims. He, therefore, directed pil­grims from Ilorin West local Government Area of the state to come to the Board in llorin on Wednesday, while Thursday was fixed for pilgrims from Asa and Ilorin South Local Government Areas. According to him, the pay­ment would be the turn of pil­grims from the Ilorin East and Moro on Friday.